I recently moved back to Manhattan after living in other states for college and work in my field, and after spending a week or two going from deli to deli in search for the best breakfast sandwich in the neighborhood, I found Broadway Bagel, and instantly felt at home again.  This establishment has and will have my loyalty for as long as I live in the UWS, and I don't think I'm alone in this either. At 8 or 9AM each day of the week, and all the way through lunchtime on weekends, there is a line that extends from the register near the entrance all the way to the beverage cooler in the back, but you'll almost never have to wait more than 10 minutes to leave with your order thanks to their attentive and friendly staff, and powerhouse of a kitchen. Seating is limited, so if you're looking to stay, you'll need to catch someone's eye or snag a seat right after it's opened up.  These are the freshest, doughiest bagels one can find in at least a 10 block radius, each with enough cream cheese to make it a perfect shmear, and their flaky chocolate (or almond) croissants are to die for.
